                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d273">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">873.00/29a: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the Minister in Switzerland</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Stovall</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-12-04T20:00:00-05:00"
                            >December 4, 1918—8 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>3447. Press reports originating in Vienna indicate that the King of Montenegro
                    has been deposed and succeeded by the National Assembly, meeting at Podgoritza.
                    The Montenegrin Minister has communicated to the Department an official despatch
                    from his Government,<note n="4" xml:id="d273fn4">
                        <hi rend="italic">Supra.</hi>
                    </note> stating that such reports had no foundation whatsoever. Please
                    investigate and report facts immediately.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Polk</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
